The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 26 November is 1,355,272 (2,407.8 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 November, there were 117,712 new confirmed cases (209.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 November, there were 154,556 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 24% (36,844 fewer cases).
